&gt; 1. Emphasize the status of the document<br>
&gt; <br>
&gt; Currently the pure ML-KEM algorithm is recommended =E2=80=9CN=E2=80=9D=
 in the IANA<br>
&gt; registry and is a non-standards-track informational document while<br>
&gt; X25519MLKEM768 is marked as recommended =E2=80=9CY=E2=80=9D and is def=
ined in a<br>
&gt; standards-track document.=C2=A0 While this indicates the preference fo=
r the<br>
&gt; hybrid approach, it was pointed out that the meaning of the =E2=80=9CN=
=E2=80=9D value<br>
&gt; may not be obvious to readers unfamiliar with the IETF process.<br>
&gt; <br>
&gt; Based on the discussion the following will be added to the IANA<br>
&gt; considerations section, which the IESG approved for pure ML-DSA, to<br=
>
&gt; save readers following existing links in the document to understand<br=
>
&gt; the meaning on N and to further addresses some hybrid/pure approach<br=
>
